<li id="cite_note-Franklin-14">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Franklin_14-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Franklin_14-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREF.5B.5BBenjamin_Franklin.5D.5D.2C_writing_.5B.5Banonymously.5D.5D1784"><a href="/wiki/Benjamin_Franklin" title="Benjamin Franklin">Benjamin Franklin</a>, writing <a href="/wiki/Anonymously" title="Anonymously" class="mw-redirect">anonymously</a> (1784-04-26). "Aux auteurs du Journal" (in French). <i>Journal de Paris</i> (117).</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Aux+auteurs+du+Journal&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+de+Paris&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BBenjamin+Franklin%5D%5D%2C+writing+%5B%5Banonymously%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BBenjamin+Franklin%5D%5D%2C+writing+%5B%5Banonymously%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1784-04-26&amp;rft.issue=117&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Daylight_saving_time"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Its first publication was in the journal's "Économie" section. The <a href="http://www.webexhibits.org/daylightsaving/franklin3.html" class="external text" title="http://www.webexhibits.org/daylightsaving/franklin3.html" rel="nofollow">revised English version</a> (retrieved on 2009-02-13) is commonly called "An Economical Project", a title that is not Franklin's; see <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFA.O._Aldridge1956">A.O. Aldridge (1956). "Franklin's essay on daylight saving". <i>American Literature</i> <b>28</b> (1): 23–29. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307%2F2922719" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307%2F2922719" rel="nofollow">10.2307/2922719</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.